race.comment: SHAQ KEEPING (1) comes here off a placing in strong time (29.72) over 520m at this track when beaten 1.75 lengths in a Grade 5. Expected to go close again if runs up to latest time. SEE THIS (3) was in the money last time at this track (30.08) in a Grade 5, finishing a 5 length third. Already a winner from this draw. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. DING'S SANDY (8) is in great form having scored back to back wins, the latest in the best of the program at Temora in 18.42. Has won two of three starts from this draw. Has definite claims.
